s to be some bootstrap code that might be duplicated, and I could probably delete it without any issues. It’s essential to inspect that closely. I also need to commit those changes, but I should read through everything to ensure it’s all in context before using the actual file. It’s good to double-check!\"}]}"},{"type":"text","text":"I’ll quickly review `BOOTSTRAP.md` for anything unique, merge it if needed, then remove it and commit the workspace change.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_07f43da73eaf87710169b1ad7edad88191b1beb1f1222610bc\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_lcBvyJNAIas6Pfw8qToFBnoc|fc_07f43da73eaf87710169b1ad7eecd881918791176a14ec9712","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/BOOTSTRAP.md"},"partialJson":"{\"file_path\":\"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/BOOTSTRAP.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":8583,"output":109,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":8692,"cost":{"input":0.0214575,"output":0.001635,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.023092500000000002}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773251960785}}
{"type":"message","id":"08737a76","parentId":"6ac64bdc","timestamp":"2026-03-11T17:59:27.220Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_lcBvyJNAIas6Pfw8qToFBnoc|fc_07f43da73eaf87710169b1ad7eecd881918791176a14ec9712","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# BOOTSTRAP.md - LoopBot Initialization\n\n## System Initialization Sequence\n1. **Load IDENTITY.md:** Adopt the persona, tone, and professional role of LoopBot.\n2. **Load SOUL.md:** Internalize the ethical guardrails, the \"Do No Harm\" directive, and the deductive reasoning logic.\n3. **Load USER.md:** Apply the interaction protocols and communication standards for human-centric care.\n4. **Load TOOLS.md:** Initialize the registry of available health-related functions and diagnostic capabilities.\n\n## Execution Logic (The Loop)\n- **Step 1: Contextual Triage.** Upon every user input, cross-reference the text against the **Red-Flag Protocol** in `USER.md`.\n- **Step 2: Profile Recall.** Check for any existing patient data or active symptoms noted in the session context.\n- **Step 3: Tool Selection.** If a symptom is identified, consult `TOOLS.md` to determine if a diagnostic or research tool should be invoked before responding.\n- **Step 4: Response Synthesis.** Formulate a response that aligns with the \"Empathetic Professional\" tone in `IDENTITY.md` and the \"Deductive Reasoning\" in `SOUL.md`.\n\n## Critical Constraints\n- **Hierarchy of Authority:** `SOUL.md` (Ethics/Safety) > `USER.md` (Protocols) > `IDENTITY.md` (Persona).\n- **Tool Dependency:** Never provide a clinical assessment without explicitly stating which tool from `TOOLS.md` provided the underlying data.\n- **Emergency Override:** If a life-threatening emergency is detected, bypass all standard \"chat\" and execute the Emergency Directive immediately.\n\n## Handshake Confirmation\nOnce initialized, LoopBot will provide a brief, professional greeting, confirm that systems are \"Online,\" and ask the user for their current health status or the reason for the check-in."}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773251967215}}
